main event: A single object was sighted over Okinawa on September 28 and 29, 1960, which appeared to be the size and color of a star.
interesting points: The object was first seen at an elevation of 15-30 degrees above the horizon, moving eastbound at 15-30 degrees per second.
The object disappeared behind a cloud bank on both occasions.
The sighting lasted for 45 seconds on September 28 and 2-3 minutes on September 29.
The report indicates the objects were likely meteors, based on the description and straight path.
The report was submitted through various military channels, including ATIC (Air Technical Intelligence Center) and PACAF (Pacific Air Forces).
